{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Implemented (staged locally, not yet pushed to Gerrit).\n\nRoot cause: explain_guide/explain_criterion read guide markdown via config.repo_root()/docs/, which resolves to the CONSUMING project's git toplevel — absent in any installed rebar → missing-file. Fixed by matching the OSS convention (verified against PyPA / scientific-python guide / certifi): runtime-needed data lives in-package, read via importlib.resources (same pattern rebar already uses for criteria_routing.json).\n\nChanges:\n- Moved both prose guides to src/rebar/_guides/{writing-a-passing-plan,passing-code-review}.md (canonical) + __init__.py. Hatchling ships them in the wheel (guarded by new test_wheel_ships_author_guides).\n- AUTHOR_GUIDES: dict[str,str] of bare filenames; explain_guide(name) resolves via resources.files('rebar._guides'), dropped repo_root_path param.\n- explain_criterion renders the section from the packaged registry via _guide_section_body (installable; overlay project criteria still resolve via load_criteria repo_root). Removed the repo-root missing-file state.\n- docs/ copies are thin pointers so existing links resolve. Dev/CI machinery (regenerate/validate_criteria_guide, coach guide_url deep-link) unchanged.\n- Tests updated to assert repo-root independence across CLI/MCP/library; added packaging tests.\n\nVerified: with REBAR_ROOT=<dir without docs/>, rebar explain plan|review|F1 all exit 0; library + MCP-shape calls succeed; both guides present as packaged resources and in the built wheel. make lint + make typecheck pass; explain/engine_dir suites green (23 passed). registry.py 714 LOC (< 800 cap).\n\nRemaining: route through Gerrit (LLM-Review + Verified) before closing — not done (awaiting go-ahead)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784747688593754001,"uuid":"21102bfc-1907-4cb1-83dc-ea4e55a93d73"}